"```sql\nSELECT AVG(attendance_count) AS average_attendance\nFROM (\n    SELECT e.event_id, COUNT(a.link_to_member) AS attendance_count\n    FROM event e\n    JOIN attendance a ON e.event_id = a.link_to_event\n    WHERE e.type = 'Meeting' AND YEAR(e.event_date) = 2020\n    GROUP BY e.event_id\n) AS meeting_attendance;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the average attendance of meetings in 2020. It first joins the `event` and `attendance` tables to count the number of members attending each meeting event in 2020. Then, it calculates the average attendance across all such meetings."